<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="42" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="3.[152,1074,230,413]" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">
REMARKS: The new species is similar to 
<taxonomicName authority="Yang &amp; Yang" authorityName="Yang &amp; Yang" box="[685,1074,230,253]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamatus">
<emphasis box="[685,913,230,253]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Platypalpus hamatus</emphasis>
Yang &amp; Yang
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingRegion box="[212,270,262,285]" country="China" name="Xizang" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">Tibet</collectingRegion>
, but it can be separated from the latter by the mesonotum with a narrow mid-longitudinal stripe and the left epandrial lamella with a weak basal process with a brush of long bristles. In 
<taxonomicName box="[432,550,326,349]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Platypalpus" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="3" pageNumber="42" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hamatus">
<emphasis box="[432,550,326,349]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="42">P. hamatus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, the mesonotum has a rather wide mid-longitudinal stripe and the basal process of the left epandrial lamella is bare (
<bibRefCitation author="YANG, D. &amp; YANG, C." pageId="3" pageNumber="42" pagination="415 - 424" refId="ref2850" refString="YANG, D. &amp; YANG, C. 1989. The dance flies of Xizang (II) (Diptera: Empididae). Acta Agriculturae Universitatis Pekinensis 15 (4): 415 - 424." type="journal article" year="1989">Yang &amp; Yang, 1989</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
